Make metadata api configurable in the library creation, if not selected fall back to the global.
User comments and reviews: Allow users to leave comments on media or chapters, and write reviews with ratings.
User profiles and avatars: Add profile pages with reading stats, favorite lists, and customizable avatars.
Following system: Let users follow other users to see their activity or shared lists.
External service sync: Sync reading progress, ratings, and lists with MyAnimeList, AniList, or MangaDex accounts.
Collections/series grouping: Group related media into custom collections (e.g., "Batman Universe" or "Shonen Jump").
Themes and UI customization: Dark/light modes, custom color schemes, or resizable panels.
Progressive Web App (PWA): Enable installation on mobile devices for a native app-like experience.
Offline reading: Cache chapters locally for offline access (especially useful for mobile).
Download support: Allow downloading chapters or entire media as archives.
Email notifications: Notify users of new chapters in followed series or library updates.
Backup and restore: Automated database backups with restore functionality.
Advanced statistics dashboard: Charts for user activity, popular media, or system performance.